# Cloudflare MCP — use cases & best practices

**Live config:** `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (install via `bash scripts/cursor-mcp-setup.sh`).  
**Repo template:** `.cursor/mcp.example.json` (HTTP URLs only, no secrets).  
**Secrets:** store `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` in Infisical — never paste tokens into chat, rules, or committed files. Optional local file cache: sync from Infisical into `app/.env.local` (gitignored) only when a stdio bridge needs a file.

Official catalog: [Cloudflare's own MCP servers](https://developers.cloudflare.com/agents/model-context-protocol/cloudflare/servers-for-cloudflare/) · API: [developers.cloudflare.com/api](https://developers.cloudflare.com/api/)

## Setup rules (do not regress)

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| **3 user servers:** `cloudflare-docs`, `cloudflare-agents-sdk`, `cloudflare-api` ([official URLs](https://developers.cloudflare.com/agents/model-context-protocol/cloudflare/servers-for-cloudflare/)) | `plugin-cloudflare-*` Cursor marketplace plugin (id `407`) — duplicates + errors |
| **OAuth** (Cursor Connect) or **API token** from Infisical for `cloudflare-api` | Test account tokens with `/user/tokens/verify` (user tokens only) |
| Account API token (`cfat_`) scoped to **Entire account** + product permissions you need | Client IP filtering on token ([unsupported by MCP](https://github.com/cloudflare/mcp)) |
| After rotating token → update Infisical → re-sync local cache if used → quit Cursor | Put shell commands in `app/.env.local` (breaks stdio MCP stdout) |

### Auth modes for `cloudflare-api`

| Mode | Config | When |
|------|--------|------|
| **OAuth** (Option 1) | `"type":"http","url":"https://mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp"` | Click **Connect** in Customize → MCP |
| **API token** (Option 2) | Bearer / stdio bridge fed from Infisical (or gitignored `.env.local` cache) | CI, account `cfat_` tokens, OAuth flaky |

`curl -I https://mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` → **401** is expected without auth.

### Verify account API token (`cfat_`)

```bash
# Prefer Infisical-injected env (never echo the token):
infisical run --env=dev -- bash -c \
  'curl -s "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN" | jq ".success, .result[].name"'

# NOT this (fails for account tokens):
# curl .../user/tokens/verify
```

## Official server map

| Server | URL | Auth |
|--------|-----|------|
| `cloudflare-api` | `https://mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | OAuth or Bearer |
| `cloudflare-docs` | `https://docs.mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | None |
| `cloudflare-agents-sdk` | `https://agents.cloudflare.com/mcp` | None |
| `cloudflare-workers-bindings` | `https://bindings.mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | OAuth/Bearer (optional bridge) |
| `cloudflare-workers-builds` | `https://builds.mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | OAuth/Bearer (optional bridge) |
| `cloudflare-observability` | `https://observability.mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | OAuth/Bearer (optional bridge) |
| `cloudflare-ai-gateway` | `https://ai-gateway.mcp.cloudflare.com/mcp` | OAuth/Bearer (optional bridge) |

**Default iPix install:** first three only. Bindings/builds/observability/ai-gateway via `cloudflare-api` `search` + `execute` unless you add optional bridges.

## Token permissions (account token on your Cloudflare account)

Your listed permissions cover the migration stack. Minimum useful sets:

| Use case | Permissions |
|----------|-------------|
| **cloudflare-api** (all REST) | Account scope + Workers Scripts, D1, KV, Pages, DNS, R2 as needed |
| **Bindings MCP** | Workers Scripts Read, D1/KV/R2 Read (+ Write to mutate) |
| **Builds MCP** | Workers CI Read |
| **Observability MCP** | Workers Observability Read, Workers Tail Read |
| **AI Gateway MCP** | AI Gateway Read |

Account tokens: include **Account** resource read (Entire account scope).

## Which server for which job

| Need | MCP server | Tool(s) |
|------|------------|---------|
| Product/docs lookup | `cloudflare-docs` | `search_cloudflare_documentation` |
| Agents SDK (DO, callable, WS) | `cloudflare-agents-sdk` | `search-agent-docs` |
| OpenAPI / endpoint shape | `cloudflare-api` | `search` |
| Live API call | `cloudflare-api` | `execute` |
| KV, D1, R2 inventory (optional) | `cloudflare-workers-bindings` | `d1_*`, `kv_*`, `r2_*`, `workers_list` |
| Build failures (optional) | `cloudflare-workers-builds` | `workers_builds_*` |
| Runtime logs (optional) | `cloudflare-observability` | `query_worker_observability` |

## Agent workflow

1. `cloudflare-docs` → 2. `cloudflare-agents-sdk` (if Agents) → 3. `cloudflare-api` `search` → 4. specialized server if installed → 5. `cloudflare-api` `execute`

## Tool patterns

**Search** (JS async arrow, `spec` in sandbox):

```javascript
async () => {
  const results = [];
  for (const [path, methods] of Object.entries(spec.paths)) {
    for (const [method, op] of Object.entries(methods)) {
      if (op.tags?.some(t => t.toLowerCase() === 'workers')) {
        results.push({ method: method.toUpperCase(), path, summary: op.summary });
      }
    }
  }
  return results.slice(0, 10);
}
```

**Execute** (`accountId` auto-bound for account tokens — use the id from `/accounts`, never hardcode):

```javascript
async () => cloudflare.request({
  method: "GET",
  path: `/accounts/${accountId}/workers/scripts`
})
```

## When MCP is unavailable

`.claude/skills/cloudflare/references/**` → [developers.cloudflare.com](https://developers.cloudflare.com) → `wrangler` CLI. Do not block **IPI-487 · CLOUDFLARE-EPIC — Cloudflare Platform Migration** on MCP.

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `plugin-cloudflare-*` errors | Quit Cursor → disable plugin Cloudflare MCP servers → reopen |
| `9109` / `Invalid access token` on execute | Rotate token in Infisical → re-sync local cache if used → quit Cursor |
| `/user/tokens/verify` → Invalid | Normal for `cfat_` — use `/accounts` instead |
| `cloudflare-api` needs auth | Connect (OAuth) or inject Bearer from Infisical |
| Stdio bridges timeout | Stay on HTTP + `cloudflare-api` only |
| `~/.cursor/mcp.json` missing / empty | `bash scripts/cursor-mcp-setup.sh` |
